{
    "analysis": "The Executor summary shows metric and trace data densely cover the full 14:00–14:30 window; error_logs are concentrated between 14:20:09 and 14:26:50 and are mostly from Tomcat nodes (Tomcat03/04/02/01). This suggests the failure likely occurred in the 14:20–14:27 sub-window and may involve Tomcat components, but we must follow the prescribed workflow: compute global thresholds on full series first, then inspect the incident window. Next we need global thresholds (e.g., P95) for each component-KPI for only the allowed root-cause components (apache01, apache02, Tomcat01-04, MG01-02, IG01-02, Mysql01-02, Redis01-02). These thresholds must be computed using the full available metric series (not yet filtered to the incident window).",
